What you need to know:

Zinedine Zidane's side had levelled through Marco Asensio midway through the second half and thought they had a penalty when Karim Benzema was brought down after rounding Sevilla goalkeeper Yassine BonoA Sevilla victory might have given them an outside chance but instead they remain six points back and are surely out of the runningMadrid still had two minutes to find a winner and they almost got it, Casemiro's effort curling agonisingly wide